\pard\f0\fs28 Very variable in habit, indumentum, pigmentation, size and shape of the leaflets and length of the calyx-teeth. Several taxa are recorded over most of Europe. Plants with smaller and less hairy calyx (3·5-4·5 mm) are often called {\b T. gracile} Thuill.,{\i   Fl. Paris} ed. 2, 383 (1799); they seem most frequent in W. Europe but occur sporadically elsewhere. {\b T. longisetum} Boiss. & Balansa in Boiss.,{\i   Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  3}({\b 6}): 47 (1859), with calyx-teeth 4-5 times as long as the tube may deserve recognition as a subspecies of the Mediterranean region.
