\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 54. T. trichopterum} Pancic,{\i   Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien}{\b  6}: 480 (1856). Like {\b 52} but leaflets 5-10 mm, obcordate-cuneate, deeply emarginate, usually persistently hairy on the lower surface; calyx with long dense, white or ultimately brown, plumose hairs, the teeth erect; corolla 5-6 mm, about 1½ times as long as the calyx.{\i   Dry stony slopes. • Balkan peninsula.} Al Bu Gr Ju.
