\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 55. T. phleoides} Pourret ex Willd.,{\i   Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 1377 (1802). Annual; stems 10-35 cm, erect, sparsely appressed-hairy. Upper leaves subsessile; leaflets 10-25 mm, linear or oblanceolate, denticulate. Stipules oblong, with a subulate apex. Heads up to 25 mm, dense, oblong, ovoid or conical, solitary or paired; peduncles 50-60 mm. Calyx-tube ovoid, with 10 distinct veins and a ring of hairs at the throat; teeth 1·5-2 mm, subequal, as long as or a little shorter than the tube, triangular-lanceolate, dilated at the base, ultimately divergent. Corolla 4-5 mm, a little shorter than the calyx.{\i   Dry, stony grassland, mainly in the mountains. S. Europe.} Al Bu Co Gr It Hs Lu Sa Si [Ga Ge].
